2022-07-07T11:58:06: Velocity area station in Southern Uplands.
Velocity area station; approx. 40m wide section. Natural section with cableway about 1km before confluence with Tweed.
Low flow control by d/s gravel riffle that is slowly accreting. Peak flow rating derived from current meter gauging up to 2.7m (about 1.2 QMED), simple extrapolation beyond.
Bypassing on left bank occurs at levels above 2m (e.g. Oct 2002), but the bypassing flows were not measured. Monthly naturalised flows available.

Southern Uplands. Relatively narrow impervious (mostly Silurian formations) catchment (half overlain by superficial deposits). Land use is mostly hill grazing, with some forested areas. Megget Reservoir (1982).
St Mary's Loch and Megget Reservoir (public water supply) have a minor impact on the flow regime.
